> Why do git stuff here?

I don't like this either and it's not needed in ORAN repo.

Then when I ported patches from ORAN to meta-starlingx here, I found the original recipe is split into several recipes:
e.g.
stx-metabl.bb -> mtce.bb, mtce-common.bb, pxe-network-installer.bb, etc

And for each recipe, it only checks out into a sub-dir, but for some recipes, it needs files in other sub-dirs, so I just follow the same way in other recipes, I thought it had been discussed and recommended.
e.g.
in https://opendev.org/starlingx/meta-starlingx/commit/15dfc29882771fef01ff1744438871d29be72671
+do_unpack_append() {
+    bb.build.exec_func('do_restore_files', d)
+}
+
+do_restore_files() {
+       cd ${S}
+       git reset ${SRCREV} bsp-files/
+       git checkout bsp-files
+}
+

